text: we ran a stack turn Norway this man is
getting up close and personal with the
local wildlife this is unfortunate
this guy has found himself in the wrong
place at the wrong time the bird is a
male Capra Kelly which is a large
species of grouse and the reason it's
attacked this guy is because it's mating
season this guy's actually walked into
what's called a breeding lek which is a
special territory that males hold in the
hopes of attracting females this was
filmed early in the morning which is
unfortunate timing because this is when
the male kappa Kelly do their mating
display they do it that time of day
because the cooler drier air means the
sound will travel further so if you'd
like to watch Capra Kelly's you're
better off waiting until the afternoon
